{"questionId":"9075031","questionHtml":"<p>Determine the orbital period for the satellite.</p>\n<p>Mass of Earth = 6.0 x 10<sup>24</sup> kg</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{m{v^2}}}{r} = G\\frac{{Mm}}{{{r^2}}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>m</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>v</mi>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mi>r</mi>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>G</mi>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>M</mi>\n      <mi>m</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>r</mi>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>leading to <em>T</em><sup>2</sup> =&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{4{\\pi ^2}{r^3}}}{{GM}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>4</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>π</mi>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>r</mi>\n          <mn>3</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>G</mi>\n      <mi>M</mi>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><em>T</em> = 5320 «s»</p>\n<p><em><strong>Alternative 2</strong></em></p>\n<p>«<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"v = \\sqrt {\\frac{{G{M_E}}}{r}} \">\n  <mi>v</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <msqrt>\n    <mfrac>\n      <mrow>\n        <mi>G</mi>\n        <mrow>\n          <msub>\n            <mi>M</mi>\n            <mi>E</mi>\n          </msub>\n        </mrow>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>r</mi>\n    </mfrac>\n  </msqrt>\n</math></span>» =&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\sqrt {\\frac{{6.67 \\times {{10}^{ - 11}} \\times 6.0 \\times {{10}^{24}}}}{{6600 \\times {{10}^3}}}} \">\n  <msqrt>\n    <mfrac>\n      <mrow>\n        <mn>6.67</mn>\n        <mo>×</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <msup>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>10</mn>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mn>11</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </msup>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>×</mo>\n        <mn>6.0</mn>\n        <mo>×</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <msup>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>10</mn>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>24</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </msup>\n        </mrow>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mn>6600</mn>\n        <mo>×</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <msup>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>10</mn>\n            </mrow>\n            <mn>3</mn>\n          </msup>\n        </mrow>\n      </mrow>\n    </mfrac>\n  </msqrt>\n</math></span>&nbsp;<em><strong>or&nbsp;</strong></em>7800 «ms<sup>–1</sup>»</p>\n<p>distance = 2<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\pi \">\n  <mi>π</mi>\n</math></span><em>r</em> = 2<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\pi \">\n  <mi>π</mi>\n</math></span> x 6600 x 10<sup>3</sup>&nbsp;«m» or 4.15 x 10<sup>7</sup>&nbsp;«m»</p>\n<p>«<em>T</em> = <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{d}{v} = \\frac{{4.15 \\times {{10}^7}}}{{7800}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>d</mi>\n    <mi>v</mi>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>4.15</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>10</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mn>7</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>7800</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>» = 5300&nbsp;«s»</p>\n<p><em>Accept use of ω instead of v</em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9075031","referenceCode":"17N.2.SL.TZ0.5a","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Determine the orbital period for the satellite. Mass of Earth = 6.0 x 1024 kg","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 6: Circular motion and gravitation","6.1 – Circular motion","Core","Topic 6: Circular motion and gravitation","6.2 – Newton’s law of gravitation","Core","Topic 6: Circular motion and gravitation"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}